claim.claim-text:
5. A method of making a microelectronic package comprising the steps of:
(a) positioning a sheet bearing a plurality of traces over an assemblage of a package substrate with conductive elements and a microelectronic element overlying the package substrate and electrically connected to the conductive elements, the positioning step being performed so that a first portion of the sheet and first portions of the traces on the first portion of the sheet extend over the microelectronic element and a second portion of the sheet and second portions of the traces on the second portion of the sheet extend from the first portion toward the package substrate;
(b) introducing a flowable composition between the sheet and the package substrate and around the microelectronic element;
(c) curing the composition to form an overmold covering the microelectronic element and having a shape at least partially defined by the sheet; and
(d) electrically connecting the second portions of the traces with the conductive elements of the package substrate.
